com.github.breadmoirai.breadbot.plugins.waiter

Interface EventActionBuilder<E extends net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.Event,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The Event Type
    V - The Result Type
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CommandEventActionBuilder<T>, EventActionBuilderExtension<E,V>, ReactionEventActionBuilder<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CommandEventActionBuilderImpl, EventActionBuilderImpl, ReactionEventActionBuilderImpl

    public interface EventActionBuilder<E extends net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.Event,V>
    A structure that allows one to wait for events. The basic control flow is 
    
  onEvent(Event e)
      if condition(e):
          action(e)
          timesRan++
          if stopper(e, timesRan):
              stopListening()
              return finisher(e)
      //otherwise continue listening

      • stopIf

        EventActionBuilder<E,V> stopIf(ObjectIntPredicate<E> stopper)
        Sets a Predicate that takes in the Event and the number of times the action has run. This is run right after the action is called. By default, this field is set with (e, i) -> true.
        Parameters:
        stopper - a predicate that takes in an Event and an int representing the number of times this action has run, returning true if this should stop listening for more events, false if it should continue to listen for events.
        Returns:
        this

      • finishWithResult

        <V2> EventActionBuilder<E,V2> finishWithResult(java.util.function.Function<E,V2> finisher)
        Sets a Function that runs after the stopper is called with the Event as the parameter, producing an Object. This allows the EventActionFuture to return a Result when it finishes waiting for events.

        By default, the finisher produces null as a result.

        Type Parameters:
        V2 - the new result Type
        Parameters:
        finisher - A Function that takes in an Event and produces a result which can be obtained through the Future,
        Returns:
        a new builder with modified generic parameters, retaining all set fields.
